b-2 inline-block","children":"2. Use Descriptive Line Items"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Vague terms like \"Design Services\" lead to questions. Questions lead to delays. Be specific: \"Logo Design - Concept Phase\" or \"Website Maintenance - January Updates.\" Clarity reduces the friction in the client's accounting department."}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 border-b-2 border-primary-500 pb-2 inline-block","children":"3. Automated Follow-Ups (The Gentle Nudge)"}],["$","p",null,{"children":["Chasing money is awkward. Let technology do it. Professional software can send a polite reminder 2 days before a due date and 24 hours after. This removes the personal stress and makes the follow-up feel like a standard business procedure rather than a confrontation. Learn more about ",["$","$L8",null,{"href":"/blog/how-to-handle-late-payments","className":"text-primary-600 hover:underline","children":"handling late payments"}],"."]}],["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 border-b-2 border-primary-500 pb-2 inline-block","children":"4. Tiered Late Fees"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Include terms in your contract for late fees. Even if you never charge them, having them on the invoice (e.g., \"1.5% monthly late fee applies after 7 days\") signals to the client that you take your business seriously. It's about setting boundaries."}]]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"bg-gray-50 p-12 rounded-[3.5rem] border border-gray-100","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-3xl font-black mb-10 text-center font-outfit","children":"Frequently Asked Questions"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-12 gap-y-8","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-gray-50","children":[["$","h4",null,{"className":"font-bold text-primary-900 mb-2","children":"Is free invoice software actually safe?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-gray-600 text-sm","children":"